Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Cathepsin G(1-5) (natural AMPs; human,  primates, mammals, animals)

Literature Information.Literature: Human neutrophil Cathepsin G is a chymotrypsin-like protease which also possesses antimicrobial activity. Antimicrobial activity is independent of the protease activity. Protease digestion of cathepsin revealed antibacterial fragments. This entry is one of them.  This peptide is active against S. aureus and N. gonorrhoeae. The orginal entry was replaced 9/2014; 9/2024.
Literature Information.Author: Bangalore N1, Travis J, Onunka VC, Pohl J, Shafer WM.1990
Literature Information.Title: Identification of the primary antimicrobial domains in human neutrophil cathepsin G.
